Atta Cave.label: Atta Cave
Atta Cave.description: The Atta Cave or Attendorn Dripstone Cave in Attendorn is one of the largest and most beautiful dripstone caves in Germany. Wikipedia

Blauhöhle.label: Blauhöhle
Blauhöhle.description: The Blauhöhle is the largest cave system in the Swabian Alps in southern Germany. The Blauhöhle presumably originated in a time when the Danube still flowed through the Blau valley. Wikipedia

Blue Grotto (Capri).label: Blue Grotto
Blue Grotto (Capri).description: The Blue Grotto is a sea cave on the coast of the island of Capri, southern Italy. Sunlight, passing through an underwater cavity and shining through the seawater, creates a blue reflection that illuminates the cavern. Wikipedia

Crag Cave.label: Crag Cave
Crag Cave.description:
Crag Cave is a cave in Ireland, located just outside Castleisland, County Kerry.
Formed in elevated limestone rock, the system extends to 3.8 kilometres of surveyed passage, on two levels. Wikipedia

Devil's Cave (near Pottenstein).label: Devil's Cave
Devil's Cave (near Pottenstein).description: The Devil's Cave is a dripstone cave located in the town of Pottenstein, Bavaria, Germany. The cave is 1,500 metres long and is the longest in Germany and the largest in Franconian Switzerland. Wikipedia

Gough's Cave.label: Gough's Cave
Gough's Cave.description: Gough's Cave is located in Cheddar Gorge on the Mendip Hills, in Cheddar, Somerset, England. The cave is 90 metres deep and is 2.135 kilometres long, and contains a variety of large chambers and rock formations. Wikipedia

Heimkehle.label: Heimkehle
Heimkehle.description: The Heimkehle is one of two great gypsum caves in Germany that are accessible as show caves. It lies on the southern edge of the Harz Mountains between Rottleberode and Uftrungen, east of Nordhausen, ... Wikipedia

Liang Bua.label: Liang Bua
Liang Bua.description: Liang Bua is a limestone cave on the island of Flores Indonesia. The site is slightly north of the town of Ruteng in Manggarai Regency in East Nusa Tenggara province. Wikipedia

Thiên Đường Cave.label: Thiên Đường Cave
Thiên Đường Cave.description: Thiên Đường Cave is a cave in Phong Nha-Kẻ Bàng National Park, UNESCO's World Heritage Site, 60 km northwest of Đồng Hới city. Wikipedia

Wookey Hole Caves.label: Wookey Hole Caves
Wookey Hole Caves.description: Wookey Hole Caves is a show cave and tourist attraction in the village of Wookey Hole on the southern edge of the Mendip Hills near Wells in Somerset, England. It is a Site of Special Scientific Interest for both biological and geological reasons. Wikipedia

Phong Nha Cave.label: Phong Nha Cave
Phong Nha Cave.description: Phong Nha Cave is a cave in Phong Nha-Kẻ Bàng National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site in Quảng Bình Province, Vietnam. It is 7,729 metres long and contains 14 grottoes, as well as a 13,969 metre underground river. Wikipedia

Postojna Cave.label: Postojna Cave
Postojna Cave.description: Postojna Cave is a 20,570 m long karst cave system near Postojna, Slovenia. It is the second-longest cave system in the country as well as one of its top tourism sites. The caves were created by the Pivka River. Wikipedia

Bakers Pit.label: Bakers Pit
Bakers Pit.description:
Bakers Pit is a phreatic maze cave system near Buckfastleigh, Devon, England.
It was first opened in 1847 by quarrying activities.
Bakers Pit is entered via a vertical descent of 16 metres. Wikipedia

Arnold Lava Tube System.label: Arnold Lava Tube System
Arnold Lava Tube System.description: The Arnold Lava Tube System is series of lava tubes within Deschutes County, Oregon, of the United States. It is located several miles southeast of the city of Bend. Wikipedia

Manor Farm Swallet.label: Manor Farm Swallet
Manor Farm Swallet.description: Manor Farm Swallet is a cave in the limestone of the Mendip Hills, in Somerset, England which was subject to numerous failed digging attempts between 1947 and 1973 as the surface shafts kept collapsing. Wikipedia

Ogof Dydd Byraf.label: Ogof Dydd Byraf
Ogof Dydd Byraf.description: Ogof Dydd Byraf is a cave which extends under Esclusham Mountain in north-east Wales from its entrance in the south face of the Minera Limeworks quarry. Wikipedia

Read's Cavern.label: Read's Cavern
Read's Cavern.description: Read's Cavern is a cave at Burrington Combe, Somerset, England, in which traces of Iron Age occupation have been found. It lies under Dolbury Hill. Its large main chamber has a boulder ruckle floor and is parallel to a cliff face. Wikipedia

Aillwee Cave.label: Aillwee Cave
Aillwee Cave.description: Aillwee Cave is a show cave located in the karst landscape of the Burren in north west County Clare, Ireland. The name Aillwee is derived from the Irish Aill Bhuí which means "yellow cliff". Wikipedia

Aveline's Hole.label: Aveline's Hole
Aveline's Hole.description:
Aveline's Hole is a cave at Burrington Combe in the limestone of the Mendip Hills, in Somerset, England.
The earliest scientifically dated cemetery in Britain was found at Aveline's Hole. Wikipedia

Boho Caves.label: Boho Caves
Boho Caves.description: The Boho Caves are a selection of caves centred on the village of Boho, County Fermanagh on the northern slopes of Belmore Mountain. They encompass the main Boho Cave and the smaller Waterfall Cave and Upper and Lower Ravine Caves. Wikipedia

Fingal's Cave.label: Fingal's Cave
Fingal's Cave.description: Fingal's Cave is a sea cave on the uninhabited island of Staffa, in the Inner Hebrides of Scotland, part of a National Nature Reserve owned by the National Trust for Scotland. Wikipedia

Gaping Gill.label: Gaping Gill
Gaping Gill.description: Gaping Gill is a natural cave in North Yorkshire, England. It is one of the unmistakable landmarks on the southern slopes of Ingleborough – a 98-metre deep pothole with the stream Fell Beck flowing into it. Wikipedia

Laas Gaal.label: Laas Gaal
Laas Gaal.description: Laas Gaal is a complex of caves and rock shelters in Somaliland, a self-declared republic that is internationally recognized as an autonomous region of Somalia. Wikipedia

Laurel Caverns.label: Laurel Caverns
Laurel Caverns.description: Laurel Caverns, formerly known as Dulaney's Cave and Laurel Hill Cave, is the largest cave in Pennsylvania. Located in Farmington, Pennsylvania; it sits on Chestnut Ridge near Uniontown, about 50 miles southeast of Pittsburgh. Wikipedia

Sea Lion Caves.label: Sea Lion Caves
Sea Lion Caves.description: Sea Lion Caves are a connected system of sea caves and caverns open to the Pacific Ocean in the U.S. state of Oregon. They are located 11 miles north of Florence on U.S. Highway 101, about midpoint on the 400 miles Oregon Coast. Wikipedia

Smoo Cave.label: Smoo Cave
Smoo Cave.description: Smoo Cave is a large combined sea cave and freshwater cave in Durness in Sutherland, Highland, Scotland. Wikipedia

Swansea Cave.label: Swansea Cave
Swansea Cave.description: Swansea Cave is a cave and palaeontological site in the Saint Catherine Parish of south-eastern Jamaica. Wikipedia

Unicorn Cave (Austria).label: Unicorn Cave
Unicorn Cave (Austria).description: The Unicorn Cave in Austria is situated in the Hohe Wand Nature Park near Dreistetten in Lower Austria and may be reached on signposted hiking trails in ca. 20 minutes from Dreistetten aus. Wikipedia

Dan yr Ogof.label: Dan yr Ogof
Dan yr Ogof.description: Dan yr Ogof, also known as the National Showcaves Centre for Wales, is a 17-kilometre long cave system in south Wales, five miles north of Ystradgynlais and fifteen miles south west of Brecon within the Brecon Beacons National Park. Wikipedia

Oxlow Cavern.label: Oxlow Cavern
Oxlow Cavern.description: Oxlow Cavern is a part-natural and part-mined cavern near Castleton in Derbyshire, England. It is situated on the south side of the road running from the A623 at Sparrowpit to the Winnats Pass, west of ... Wikipedia

Dunmore Cave.label: Dunmore Cave
Dunmore Cave.description: Dunmore Cave is a limestone solutional cave in Ballyfoyle, County Kilkenny, Ireland. It is formed in Lower Carboniferous limestone of the Clogrenan Formation. Wikipedia

Xueyu Cave.label: Xueyu Cave
Xueyu Cave.description: Xueyu Cave is a National Three Gorges Scenic Area and a National 4A Scenic Area located in Fengdu County, Chongqing Municipality, People's Republic of China. Wikipedia

Cave of Reveillon.label: Cave of Reveillon
Cave of Reveillon.description: The Cavern of Reveillon is a French cave located near Alvignac. Wikipedia

Mitchell Caverns.label: Mitchell Caverns
Mitchell Caverns.description: The Mitchell's Caverns, within the Mitchell Caverns Natural Preserve, are a trio of limestone caves, located on the east side of the Providence Mountains at an elevation of 4,300 feet, within the Providence Mountains State Recreation Area. Wikipedia

Sinks of Gandy.label: Sinks of Gandy
Sinks of Gandy.description: The Sinks of Gandy — also called the Sinks of Gandy Creek, or simply “The Sinks” — are a modestly celebrated cave and underground stream at Osceola in eastern Randolph County, West Virginia, USA. Wikipedia

Thor's Cave.label: Thor's Cave
Thor's Cave.description: Thor's Cave is a natural cavern located at SK09865496 in the Manifold Valley of the White Peak in Staffordshire, England. It is classified as a Karst cave. Wikipedia

Bluff Dweller's Cave.label: Bluff Dweller's Cave
Bluff Dweller's Cave.description: Bluff Dweller's Cave is a show cave located in Noel, Missouri. It was developed by channels of water flowing through joints in the Saint Joe Limestone during the Paleozoic Era. Wikipedia

Optymistychna Cave.label: Optymistychna Cave
Optymistychna Cave.description: Optymistychna is a gypsum cave located near the Ukrainian village of Korolivka, Borschiv Raion, Ternopil Oblast. As of 2005, it has 230 km of mapped passageways and is the longest cave in Eurasia. Wikipedia

Attborough Swallet.label: Attborough Swallet
Attborough Swallet.description:
Attborough Swallet is a cave in Chewton Mendip in Somerset, England.
It is unusual for a cave on the Mendip Hills in that it is not in limestone but instead in Dolomitic Conglomerate and Marl. Wikipedia

Blanche Cave.label: Blanche Cave
Blanche Cave.description: Blanche Cave, previously known as "The Big Cave", "The Old Cave" and "Mosquito Plains Cave", is one of 26 caves to be found in the Naracoorte Caves National Park, a World Heritage listed site. Wikipedia

Cave of the Crystals.label: Cave of the Crystals
Cave of the Crystals.description: Cave of the Crystals or Giant Crystal Cave is a cave connected to the Naica Mine 300 metres below the surface in Naica, Chihuahua, Mexico. The main chamber contains giant selenite crystals, some of the largest natural crystals ever found. Wikipedia

Gökgöl Cave.label: Gökgöl Cave
Gökgöl Cave.description: Gökgöl Cave is a cave in Zonguldak Province, Turkey Wikipedia

Gruta das Torres.label: Gruta das Torres
Gruta das Torres.description: The Gruta das Torres, is a lava cave, a geological formation of volcanic origin formed from the flow and cooling of subterranean magma rivers. Wikipedia

Huanglong Cave.label: Huanglong Cave
Huanglong Cave.description: Huanglong Cave is a karst cave located near the Wulingyuan district of Zhangjiajie City, Hunan, People's Republic of China and a national 4A rated scenic area. As of 2010, the cave has over a million visitors per year. Wikipedia

Lava River Cave (Arizona).label: Lava River Cave
Lava River Cave (Arizona).description: Lava River Cave is a lava tube cave in northern Arizona's Coconino National Forest. At approximately 0.75-mile long, it is the longest cave of this kind known in Arizona. The cave was discovered by some lumbermen in 1915. Wikipedia

Mud Caves.label: Mud Caves
Mud Caves.description: The Mud Caves are a popular feature in Anza Borrego Desert State Park in San Diego County, California. Wikipedia

Lovelock Cave.label: Lovelock Cave
Lovelock Cave.description: Lovelock Cave is a North American archaeological site previously known as Sunset Guano Cave, Horseshoe Cave, and Loud Site 18. The cave is about 150 feet long and 35 feet wide. Wikipedia

Naj Tunich.label: Naj Tunich
Naj Tunich.description:
Naj Tunich is a natural cave and an important archaeological site in Guatemala.
The discovery of the Naj Tunich caves, in Poptún southern Peten, Guatemala, in 1979 initiated the interest for Cave Archeology among Mayanists. Wikipedia

Notts Pot.label: Notts Pot
Notts Pot.description: Notts Pot is cave system on Leck Fell, Lancashire, England. It is described as 'the most concentrated vertical maze in Britain'. Wikipedia

Longwood Swallet.label: Longwood Swallet
Longwood Swallet.description:
Longwood Swallet is a cave near Charterhouse, in the Carboniferous Limestone of the Mendip Hills, in Somerset, England. The cave is part of the Cheddar Complex SSSI and connected to August Hole.
It is 1.65 km in length and reaches a depth of 175m. Wikipedia

Ogof Nadolig.label: Ogof Nadolig
Ogof Nadolig.description: Ogof Nadolig is a cave in the Alyn Gorge near Cilcain, Flintshire, Wales. It is mostly crawling, 300 metres long, and ends with a shaft up to the surface and a locked manhole cover. Wikipedia

Otter Hole.label: Otter Hole
Otter Hole.description: Otter Hole is perhaps one of the best decorated caves in Britain. Located on the English Welsh border just north of Chepstow, the cave runs from the banks of the tidal River Wye under the Chepstow ... Wikipedia

Sima Humboldt.label: Sima Humboldt
Sima Humboldt.description: Sima Humboldt is an enormous sinkhole located on the summit of the plateau of Sarisariñama tepui in Bolívar State, Venezuela. Wikipedia

Sima Martel.label: Sima Martel
Sima Martel.description: Sima Martel is an enormous sinkhole located on the summit of plateau of Sarisariñama tepui, in Bolívar State, Venezuela. Wikipedia

Sima de las Cotorras.label: Sima de las Cotorras
Sima de las Cotorras.description: Sima de las Cotorras, Spanish for Sinkhole of Parrots, is a giant circular sinkhole in the karst plateau of the Mexican state of Chiapas. Wikipedia

Slaughter Stream Cave.label: Slaughter Stream Cave
Slaughter Stream Cave.description:
Slaughter Stream Cave, also known as Wet Sink, is a cave system in the Wye Valley, Forest of Dean.
A series of fixed ladders and two pitches lead to sporting streamways, sandy crawls and fossil passages. Wikipedia

Taiji Cave.label: Taiji Cave
Taiji Cave.description: Taiji Cave is a karst cave located on Shilong Mountain in Guangde County, Xuancheng City, Anhui Province, People's Republic of China, where the provinces of Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Anhui meet. Wikipedia

Beer Quarry Caves.label: Beer Quarry Caves
Beer Quarry Caves.description: Beer Quarry Caves is a man-made limestone underground complex located about a mile west of the village of Beer, Devon, and the main source in England for beer stone. Wikipedia

Gouffre Jean-Bernard.label: Gouffre Jean-Bernard
Gouffre Jean-Bernard.description: Gouffre Jean-Bernard or Réseau Jean Bernard, sometimes known simply as Jean Bernard, is one of the deepest known caves in the world. It is found in the Alps, in Samoëns, France. Wikipedia

Ogof Ffynnon Ddu.label: Ogof Ffynnon Ddu
Ogof Ffynnon Ddu.description: Ogof Ffynnon Ddu is a cave located under a hillside in the area surrounding Penwyllt in the Upper Swansea Valley in South Wales. At 308 metres deep and 50 kilometres long, it is the deepest cave in the UK and the second longest in Wales. Wikipedia

Spannagel Cave.label: Spannagel Cave
Spannagel Cave.description: The Spannagel Cave is a show cave near Hintertux, in the Zillertal Alps in the Austrian state of Tyrol. Currently about 10 kilometres of cave have been discovered; guided tours enable access to 500 metres of the cave. Wikipedia

Speedwell Cavern.label: Speedwell Cavern
Speedwell Cavern.description:
The Speedwell Cavern is one of the four show caves in Castleton, Derbyshire, England.
It consists of a horizontal lead miners' adit leading to the cavern itself, a limestone cave. Wikipedia

Blue Grotto (Biševo).label: Blue Grotto
Blue Grotto (Biševo).description: The Blue Grotto or Blue Cave, is a water-logged sea cave located in a small bay called Balun, on the east side of the island of Biševo and about 4.5 nautical miles from Komiža, in the Croatian Adriatic. Wikipedia

Bad Hole Cave.label: Bad Hole Cave
Bad Hole Cave.description: Bad Hole Cave is an impressively large rising cave in the Cockpit Country of Jamaica. This is a limestone Karst region that is very rich in caves. Wikipedia

Coffee River Cave.label: Coffee River Cave
Coffee River Cave.description: Coffee River Cave is a large river cave in Manchester Parish in west-central Jamaica. It is 2800 metres in length and at an altitude of 250 metres. Wikipedia

GB Cave.label: GB Cave
GB Cave.description: GB Cave is a cave between Charterhouse and Shipham in the limestone of the Mendip Hills, in Somerset, England, and is close to Charterhouse Cave, the deepest in the region. Wikipedia

Goatchurch Cavern.label: Goatchurch Cavern
Goatchurch Cavern.description: Goatchurch Cavern is a cave on the edge of Burrington Combe in the limestone of the Mendip Hills, in Somerset, England. Wikipedia

Hutchinson's Hole.label: Hutchinson's Hole
Hutchinson's Hole.description: Hutchinson's Hole is a large sinkhole named after the 18th century serial killer Lewis Hutchinson, who used the sinkhole to dispose of bodies. Wikipedia

Sinkhole Dersios.label: Dersios sinkhole
Sinkhole Dersios.description:
The Dersios sinkhole is a sinkhole in Arcadia, Greece.
The sinkhole, which has a depth of 170 metres, has been known since antiquity and is located towards the north end of the plateau of Palaiochora ... Wikipedia

Morgans Pond Hole.label: Morgans Pond Hole
Morgans Pond Hole.description: At 186 metres, Morgans Pond Hole in Manchester Parish, Jamaica is the second deepest known cave in the island. Wikipedia

White Scar Caves.label: White Scar Cave
White Scar Caves.description: White Scar Caves is a show cave in the civil parish of Ingleton, North Yorkshire, England, under Ingleborough in the Chapel-le-Dale valley of the Yorkshire Dales National Park. Wikipedia

Jiangzhou Cave System.label: Jiangzhou Cave System
Jiangzhou Cave System.description:
Jiangzhou Cave System is a cave system near Jiangzhou township, in Fengshan County, Guangxi, China.
This cave has several entrances, with a total of 29.2 km of passages having been surveyed. Wikipedia

Luobi Cave.label: Luobi Cave
Luobi Cave.description: Luobi Cave is a karst cave under the west face of Yin Ridge located 7 km north east of Lizhigou Town, 15 km from Sanya City, Hainan Province, People's Republic of China. Wikipedia

Neffs Cave (Utah).label: Neffs Cave
Neffs Cave (Utah).description: Neffs Cave is a cave in Neffs Canyon on the north side of Mount Olympus, Utah, in the United States. It is one of the deepest caves in the United States but is seldom entered despite its depth and its close proximity to Salt Lake City, Utah. Wikipedia

Pollnagollum.label: Pollnagollum
Pollnagollum.description: Pollnagollum–Poulelva is an active stream passage cave situated in County Clare, Ireland. Wikipedia

Gourie Cave.label: Gourie Cave
Gourie Cave.description: Gourie Cave is a large river cave in Manchester Parish in west-central Jamaica. At 3505 metres it is the longest cave known in the island. It is liable to flooding. Wikipedia

Jackson's Bay Cave.label: Jackson's Bay Cave
Jackson's Bay Cave.description: Jackson's Bay Cave is a very large cave system on the Portland Ridge in Clarendon near the south coast of Jamaica. It is considered to be one of the most beautiful in the Caribbean. Wikipedia

Rod's Pot.label: Rod's Pot
Rod's Pot.description:
Rod's Pot is a limestone cave above Burrington Combe in the Mendip Hills, in Somerset, England.
The cave was first excavated in 1944 by the University of Bristol Spelæological Society. Wikipedia

Traungold Cave.label: Traungold Cave
Traungold Cave.description: Traungold Cave is a cave which has provided shelter and storage space to the Cambridge University Caving Club during their expeditions to Austria. Wikipedia

Abrakurrie Cave.label: Abrakurrie Cave
Abrakurrie Cave.description: Abrakurrie Cave is a wild cave on the Nullarbor Plain in Western Australia. It is reported to have the largest single cave chamber in the southern hemisphere, and that stencils in the cave are the ... Wikipedia

Batatotalena Cave.label: Batatotalena Cave
Batatotalena Cave.description: The Batatotalena Cave, also known as the Diva Guhava in Buddhist literature, is a cave system in Sudagala, 5 km away from the town of Kuruwita, in the Sabaragamuwa Province of Sri Lanka. Wikipedia

Ear of Dionysius.label: Ear of Dionysius
Ear of Dionysius.description: The Ear of Dionysius is a limestone cave carved out of the Temenites hill in the city of Syracuse, on the island of Sicily in Italy. Its name comes from its similarity in shape to the human ear. Wikipedia

Easegill System.label: Easegill System
Easegill System.description: The Ease Gill Cave System is the longest, and most complex cave system in Britain, with around 41 miles of passages, including connections only passable by cave diving. It spans the valley between Leck Fell and Casterton Fell. Wikipedia

Gargantua (cave).label: Gargantua
Gargantua (cave).description: Gargantua is a limestone cave located on the Andy Good Plateau in British Columbia, Canada. As of 2002 it has 6001 m of passages with a depth of 286 m. It contains the largest natural cavern in Canada at 290m long, 30m wide and 25m high. Wikipedia

Jogeshwari Caves.label: Jogeshwari Caves
Jogeshwari Caves.description: The Jogeshwari Caves are some of the earliest Hindus and Buddhist cave temples sculptures located in the Mumbai suburb of Jogeshwari, India. The caves date back to 520 to 550 CE. Wikipedia

Ogof Craig a Ffynnon.label: Ogof Craig a Ffynnon
Ogof Craig a Ffynnon.description:
Ogof Craig a Ffynnon is a cave in Wales. The cave is about 7 km in length.
The cave is renowned as one of the most well-decorated caves in Britain. Wikipedia

Lost River Caverns.label: Lost River Caverns
Lost River Caverns.description: Lost River Caverns is a natural limestone cavern consisting of 5 chambers. The caverns were formed by the karstification or dissolving of the limestone by water. In the past the caverns have been called Rentzeimer's Cave and Lost Cave. Wikipedia

Seneca Caverns (Ohio).label: Seneca Caverns
Seneca Caverns (Ohio).description: Seneca Caverns is a show cave located in northeastern Seneca County, Ohio, USA, just outside of Flat Rock. The cave is designated as a Registered Natural Landmark by the Ohio Department of Natural Resources. Wikipedia

Llygad Llwchwr.label: Llygad Llwchwr
Llygad Llwchwr.description: Llygad Llwchwr is a 1.2 km long cave system in the Black Mountain which forms the westernmost range of the Brecon Beacons National Park in Wales. Wikipedia
